Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows significant renal dysfunction (elevated creatinine), proteinuria, and abnormal urine findings (cloudy, brown, low specific gravity, ketonuria, glucosuria), with low blood glucose and HbA1c, and mild metabolic acidosis (low CO₂). These findings suggest acute or chronic kidney injury with possible nephrotic features and metabolic derangements. Urgent clinical evaluation and nephrology referral are recommended.
